can't portray much meaning through a text message and that is one of the main disadvantages to texting rather than a 
phone call. 

Messages that were sent on a monthly basis exploded from 14 billion in 2000 to 188 billion in 2010. It is isane to think 
how much people text now and all of those potential miscommunicaions.

This can also be taken into emailing as well, the amount of times that I have recieved emails from clients and thought to 
myself what does he mean by that? When a quick phone call could have cleared it up rather than me sitting there thinking 
the worst. The obvious fear is that there needs to be a balance between what we use for communication and make sure that 
we do not become socially inept.

With all that being said there is obvoiusly a massive amount of possitve effects of texting and communication for example
