I have researched the effects that social media has had on communication in terms of the way we are now starting to act
through communication. I also came across the same website as Jordan for this so I then moved on to looking at how social
media started to change the way in which we communicate and how that has developed over the past few years which I 
quite interesting!

I came across this website http://www.e-guillotine.com/how-social-media-changed-the-way-we-interact-with-the-world.php

This website talks about how social media helps us to communicate with a wider range of people from all over the world
compared to before we had social media networks, where our resources were more limited. 

One advatage to this is that it means we can get the opinions of a lot more people with the click of a button.This
makes it easier for people to get their messages across to people, where as before hand you would have to speak to
someone dirct to beable to get your message out.

This website also states that there are also down sides to social networking which is we tend to group with people who have
the same opinions as us over the web, this leaves us a little bit unexposed to other peoples opinions and thoughts.

Another downside to the development of social networking is that we are starting to lose our communication skills when 
talking to people face to face and this is because we are so used to sitting silently typing out our thoughts that we
are starting to forget how to portray these in real life situations rather than interacting online. 

I also agree with this website as you can see this occuring in every day situations where people can get easily offended
or do not know how to approach a situation because they are getting less and less used to communicating face to face.




